<br>
Rogues as fast swinging fighters have no tripple attack<br>
Paladins / Shadow Knights as tanks have no defensive disc<br>
<br>
The reasons for Rogues not getting it are that VI considers them overpowered allready anyways and that they would exceed the 1.4 damage ratio to Warriors by far with it.<br>
The reasons Paladins / Shadow Knights don't get it are that they have buffs and heals. Ok, in the 50+ game, where the discs would be in effect, how often is the Paladin the buffer and not the Cleric and if so, would the Paladin only selfbuff and leave the Warrior aside? How many Cleric buffs or Heals does a Shadow Knight have? If Pal/SK would be maintank of a group, how often have you seen them heal themselves while a Warrior, Monk or Rogue use their discs all the time?<br>
<br>
Versatility means near to nothing in EQ, it's a nice-to-have sometimes but Never a must-have. You can easily compare the efficiency of 2 groups Cle/War/Enc and Dru/Pal/Enc in a 50+ dungeon, and you will see a giant gap between both groups.<br>
The damageshield of the Druid will certainly get the dmg output of a 2HS wielding Paladin equal to the dualwielding Warrior, but the Paladin will take many, many more hard hits even while chain-stunning and the Druid will be chain healing to compensate that (Enc is just for CC and C2 in this example). This means, 2 specialists are still more than 2 highly versatile classes - not only in raid-situations but also in xp groups. Arguing with soloing might be a point when comparing Druid with Cleric, but the melee gear allows Warriors to solo nearly as well as a Paladin. War takes less and less hard hits, downs a mob with his higher dmg a lot faster, then regains HP with Fungi or similar stuff. During that the Paladin chain stuns only to survive the encounter long enough to kill, then meds up, then heals up, then meds up again - one meditation session can be canceled if the Paladin has the very time draining DW helm.<br>
With SKs it is similar, so what's the point?<br>
<br>
No, don't think that I am ranting against Rogues here or whining for oh-so-poor Paladins, but class balance was broken, is broken and will be broken as long as all and every class is as desireble for raids and groups like Cle/Enc, and maybe has some solo-power too. Make it categorie of classes (healer, tank, dmg-dealer, caster, utility caster??) and it's the same.<br>
